             was indicted for <rs id="t17890225-21-off101" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17890225-21-off101" type="offenceCategory" value="violentTheft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17890225-21-off101" type="offenceSubcategory" value="highwayRobbery"></interp>
               feloniously assaulting 
                     <persName id="t17890225-21-victim293" type="victimName">
                        William 
                        Aldridge
                     <interp inst="t17890225-21-victim293" type="surname" value="Aldridge"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17890225-21-victim293" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17890225-21-victim293" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                  , on the King's highway, on the <rs id="t17890225-21-cd102" type="crimeDate">30th of January</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17890225-21-off101 t17890225-21-cd102"></join> last, and putting him in fear, and feloniously taking from his person, and against his will, six cut glass crewets, with gilt letters therein, value 15 s. and ten ditto, value 17 s. 6 d. the property of 
                     <persName id="t17890225-21-victim294" type="victimName">
                        George 
                        Blakeway
                     <interp inst="t17890225-21-victim294" type="surname" value="Blakeway"></interp>
