             sworn. </p>
               <p>I am in partnership with 
               <persName id="t17890225-21-person301">
                  John
                   Hodsdon
               <interp inst="t17890225-21-person301" type="surname" value="Hodsdon"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17890225-21-person301" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17890225-21-person301" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , we are glass-cutters in the Strand. It appearing in this stage of the trial, that <rs id="t17890225-21-verdict106" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17890225-21-verdict106" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17890225-21-verdict106" type="verdictSubcategory" value="fault"></interp>
               the name of "Hodsdon" was spelt "Hodsdons" in the indictment, the prisoner was ACQUITTED
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>Tried by the London Jury before Mr. Justice GROSE.</p>
               <p>Ordered by the Court to be detained to be tried on a fresh indictment.</p>
